Its goal is to return the drivers behind the wheel, so the drivers will also have to complete a transport retraining course.
In addition to the National Transportation Safety Authority, the General Directorate of Transportation (DGT) and the Foundation of the Institute of Technology for Automobile Safety (FITSA) will also participate in this experience.
According to statistics, between 30 and 75 % of drivers accused more than once of driving drunk again in this state sit behind the wheel.
Alcoholock should prevent this, as it is a system connected to a vehicle that measures the level of alcohol in the breathable air and prevents the car from starting if the driver is not breathing before or if the alcohol concentration is higher than allowed.
His price is more than 1,000 euros and he would have to pay it himself.
A study conducted in this sense in the US in 2007 showed that in vehicles equipped with these devices, violations were reduced by 65% during the first year since the introduction.
In Spain, it is estimated that 115 people could be saved every year.
The measure is limited to administrative sanctions for two reasons: to resolve this behaviour before it results in a criminal offence.
And in order to facilitate its implementation, since legal regulation can be carried out in the usual way, the necessary modification of penal provisions requires a change of law.
The device is not yet available on the Spanish market in any sales version, although in some industrial vehicles and public service vehicles it has already been installed experimentally.
